item.dc:creator: @sanga282 sanga282
item.description:
@sanga282 wrote:

The cook from runescape:

Surely they aren’t having private lines for different customers that’s crazy shit! I like my ISP because it’s free, it’s just the standard up-to-8mb package from BT. If companies like virgin are slowly fitting fibre optic cables for their customers, eventually enough people will purchase it around my area to just give the area high speed? I doubt they’ll give everyone their own fibre optic cable and leave me running on a single copper wire to the ISP.

no the line will be under ground and you just get a tap into it, virgin have fibre optic wires in most built up areas so you should get it unless, like i said, you live in the highlands. Virgin dont even do a copper broadand option now( or at least not that i know of) so if you go with virgin and they give the ok you will get some pretty decent speeds
